posts.title: Last night I witnessed the path forward in 2028
posts.content:
With the exception of insect landings and occasional one-liners VP debates are an utter snooze fest.

Last night's debate changed the VP debate status quo by providing one answer to the question many MAGA and mainstream conservatives continue to ask.

What does MAGA look like beyond 2028?

JD Vance won the debate for many reasons, but ultimately it came down to a question never asked, but profoundly answered:

Is he Presidential material?

Absolutely.

In the debate he proved this by:

  • Keeping his poise and composure during a heated debate viewed globally.

  • Modeling what a warrior gentleman looks like in contrast to the GOP's pushover gentleman.

  • Being gracious and appreciative to not only Walz, but Walz's ideas, even when he had profound disagreements with them.

  • By not "going there" on so many attack points that Walz had obviously devoted much time prepping a response for, showing a strategy focused on higher priorities.

  • Finally answering by answering the the #1 question by looking presidential from start to finish.

By his outstanding debate performance JD Vance validated Trump's wisdom in choosing him as a running mate and cementing a potential path forward to continue MAGA's efforts beyond 2028.

While he remains a viable candidate for 2028, Vance's immediate contribution is further building the case to Make America Great Again in 2024. This is our focus and action in the days ahead.
